"title": "4510: sowing and reaping",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4510",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>OT references are mainly agricultural with regulatory laws covering crop production and festivals of thanksgiving. God's blessing was reflected in the harvest. The NT refers more to the spiritual sowing and reaping that takes place in the kingdom of God.</p>\n<h2>Regulations concerning the sowing and reaping of crops</h2>\n<h3>Laws of purity related to planting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:23-Lev19:25\">LEV 19:23–19:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:9\">DEU 22:9</a></p>\n<h3>Reapers are to leave gleanings for the poor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:9-Lev19:10\">LEV 19:9–19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:22\">LEV 23:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:19\">DEU 24:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:2-Ruth2:3\">RUT 2:2–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:15-Ruth2:16\">RUT 2:15–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Harvest celebrations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:16\">EXO 23:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:9-Lev23:11\">LEV 23:9–23:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:39-Lev23:41\">LEV 23:39–23:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:9-Deut16:10\">DEU 16:9–16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:13-Deut16:15\">DEU 16:13–16:15</a></p>\n<h3>The Sabbath-rest for the land and its cultivators</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:10-Exod23:11\">EXO 23:10–23:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:21\">EXO 34:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:3-Lev25:5\">LEV 25:3–25:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:11\">LEV 25:11</a></p>\n<h2>Reaping a good harvest is a blessing from God</h2>\n<h3>It is a consequence of obedience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:12\">GEN 26:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:18-Lev25:22\">LEV 25:18–25:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:3-Lev26:5\">LEV 26:3–26:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:10\">LEV 26:10</a></p>\n<h3>It is a promise to the remnant of God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:13-Amos9:14\">AMO 9:13–9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:23\">ISA 30:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:8-Isa62:9\">ISA 62:8–62:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:21-Isa65:22\">ISA 65:21–65:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:5\">JER 31:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:11-Zech8:12\">ZEC 8:11–8:12</a></p>\n<h2>God's judgment on Israel is reflected in reaping a poor harvest</h2>\n<h3>A poor yield of crops</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:18-Lev26:20\">LEV 26:18–26:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15\">DEU 28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:38-Deut28:40\">DEU 28:38–28:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:10\">ISA 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:10-Isa17:11\">ISA 17:10–17:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:13\">JER 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:13\">JER 12:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:6\">HAG 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:10-Hag1:11\">HAG 1:10–1:11</a></p>\n<h3>The harvesting of one's crops by others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:15-Lev26:16\">LEV 26:15–26:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:36-Neh9:37\">NEH 9:36–9:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:7-Job31:8\">JOB 31:7–31:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:17\">JER 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:15\">MIC 6:15</a></p>\n<h2>Proverbs and poems of sowing and harvest</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:5\">PRO 10:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:4\">PRO 20:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:23-Isa28:29\">ISA 28:23–28:29</a></p>\n<h2>Moral and spiritual sowing and reaping</h2>\n<h3>Good and evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:8\">JOB 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:18\">PRO 11:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:8\">PRO 22:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:7\">HOS 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:12-Hos10:13\">HOS 10:12–10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:7-Gal6:8\">GAL 6:7–6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:18\">JAS 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Sowing and reaping in the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:3-Mark4:8\">MRK 4:3–4:8</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:3-Matt13:8\">MAT 13:3–13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:5-Luke8:8\">LUK 8:5–8:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:18-Matt13:23\">MAT 13:18–13:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:14-Mark4:20\">MRK 4:14–4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:11-Luke8:15\">LUK 8:11–8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:24-Matt13:30\">MAT 13:24–13:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:37-Matt13:39\">MAT 13:37–13:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:26-Mark4:29\">MRK 4:26–4:29</a></p>\n<h3>The certainty of reaping</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps126:5-Ps126:6\">PSA 126:5–126:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:9\">GAL 6:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Reaping where others have sown</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:35-John4:38\">JHN 4:35–4:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:13\">ROM 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:5-1Cor3:9\">1CO 3:5–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Reaping a material harvest from spiritual sowing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:9-1Cor9:11\">1CO 9:9–9:11</a></p>\n<h2>People and nations are reaped for judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:13\">JOL 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:33\">JER 51:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:11\">HOS 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:15-Rev14:19\">REV 14:15–14:19</a></p>\n<h2>Metaphorical use of sowing and reaping</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:7\">ISA 5:1–5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:4-Isa17:6\">ISA 17:4–17:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:3\">JER 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:21\">JER 2:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:35-1Cor15:44\">1CO 15:35–15:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:6-2Cor9:11\">2CO 9:6–9:11</a></p>",
